sentences: Jay Hoggard (born September 24, 1954) is an American jazz vibraphonist.
He worked with Anthony Davis and Leo Smith in the early 1970s in New England.
After moving to New York City in 1977, he worked again with Davis and with Chico Freeman, Sam Rivers, Cecil Taylor, James Newton, and Kenny Burrell.
He has appeared on television on CBS Sunday Morning and BET Jazz.
